cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.AR

The paper discusses network function virtualization (NFV) which is a topic related to computer networks and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the relationship between NFV and software-defined networking (SDN) and cloud computing, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY) respectively. The paper also discusses the state-of-the-art in NFV, which involves the development of new architectures, systems, and applications, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR).
